'''''Battle for Normandy''''' is a [[computer wargame]] published in 1982 by [[Strategic Simulations]].

==Gameplay==
''Battle for Normandy'' is a game in which the operations from the landing at Normandy up through the build-up that led to [[Operation Cobra]] is simulated.<ref name="CGW9"/>

==Reception==
''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' reviewed the game and stated that "Overall, Battle for Normandy is an enjoyable game that will allow multiple playings and repeated playings with equal satisfaction."<ref name="CGW9">{{cite magazine |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Mar–Apr 1983 |volume=1 |issue=9 |pages=44}}</ref>

Robert S. Cauthorn for the ''[[Arizona Daily Star]]'' said that "The game is difficult to learn at the beginning, but once rolling, it is thrilling - and teaches players a good deal about the invasion itself."<ref>{{cite web|first=Robert S.|last=Cauthorn|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/arizona-daily-star/123500839/|title=A sample screening of some of the non-arcade computer games|newspaper=[[Arizona Daily Star]]|page=77|date=January 15, 1984|accessdate=|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>

